ce:section.ce:para:
First, 0.5 g gallic acid and 200 μL EDA (ethylenediamine) was dissolved in 20 mL of DMF at 50–55 °C for 10 min.; then, the solution was transferred into a Teflon-lined stainless-steel hydrothermal vessel. After heating the solution at 200 °C for 12 h, it was cooled to room temperature and centrifuged at 8000 rpm for 30 min to remove high-weight precipitate and agglomerated particles. Further, the solution was filtered using a 0.22 μm syringe filter prior subjected to characterization and stored at 4 °C for further use. The synthetic method is represented in Scheme 1
                         (Fig. 1
                        ).
